

1.To Install php driver for mongo...
  -> sudo /opt/lampp/bin/pecl install mongo
       
         IF
    if auto config Error:
  ->  autoconf
  ->  sudo apt-get install autoconf
       
     Again Do:
  ->  sudo /opt/lampp/bin/pecl install mongo

            
  
       IF
  if compiler library not install ERROR:
  ->  sudo apt-get install libssl-dev 
  ->  sudo /opt/lampp/bin/pecl install mongo
 

2.To get root privillege
   ->  sudo -i

3.To add extention
  
 -> echo 'extension=mongo.so' >> /opt/lampp/etc/php.ini

 exit from root
  ->exit

run sample php code for connectivity which should be saved on htdocs folder for XAMPP 
and if u r using only apache then save this file to var/www/
